<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="3">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="3">
Males of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mahdiaensis">Rivulus mahdiaensis</taxonomicName>
differ from all other species of the genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7737CC47-FB47-4DAF-87C2-18950BAD40FA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus Poey 1860:307" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rivulus</taxonomicName>
by their unique long and lyre-shaped caudal fin with filaments and by the elongated unpaired fins.
</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageNumber="4" pageNumber="3">
Females show a narrow dark lateral band and share this distinctive characteristic only with 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:37E63DF1-2EF0-4BA6-BF0B-B292F82522C9" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus frenatus Eigenmann 1912:453, 455" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="frenatus">Rivulus frenatus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:80210F02-FBC9-4A97-A95B-296874194674" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus xiphidius Huber 1979:66" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="xiphidius">R. xiphidius</taxonomicName>
and perhaps 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F88985D8-B482-4EBD-A7AB-97270DDC9F8F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus campelloi Costa 1990:42" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="campelloi">R. campelloi</taxonomicName>
(Huber 1992). Females of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mahdiaensis">Rivulus mahdiaensis</taxonomicName>
have an ocellus on the dorsal part of the caudal peduncle. This is unusual because the small species of the Guyana plateau have no ocellus on the caudal peduncle. This ocellus is often present in females of many species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7737CC47-FB47-4DAF-87C2-18950BAD40FA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus Poey 1860:307" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rivulus</taxonomicName>
and hence is often called a “ 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7737CC47-FB47-4DAF-87C2-18950BAD40FA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus Poey 1860:307" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rivulus</taxonomicName>
spot”. The meristics (D 6-7, A 8-9 and D/A 4-5) (Table 1) are lower than those of the other small species on the Guyana plateau (Table 2).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="4">
Comparison of mitochondrial DNA sequences place this species as a member of a monophyletic clade which includes 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:C85063FD-B6D1-4505-A11A-2808251D256A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus agilae Hoedeman 1954:203" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="agilae">R. agilae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:FBA3D378-1C49-443A-A0E2-E8F9EE0E5BE4" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus geayi Vaillant 1899:156 [3]" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="geayi">geayi Vaillant</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:37E63DF1-2EF0-4BA6-BF0B-B292F82522C9" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus frenatus Eigenmann 1912:453, 455" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="frenatus">frenatus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:80210F02-FBC9-4A97-A95B-296874194674" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus xiphidius Huber 1979:66" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="xiphidius">xiphidius Huber</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:5667AFB0-869D-44D2-9686-7CBA1A0114EE" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus lyricauda Thomerson, Berkenkamp &amp; Taphorn 1991:290" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lyricauda">lyricauda Thomerson, Berkenkamp &amp; Taphorn</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mahdiaensis">R. mahdiaensis</taxonomicName>
possesses a unique karyotype (2n=38) among members of this group.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="4">Description</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="4">
This new species is small and slender and has a uniquely shaped caudal fin. All rays of the caudal are proportionately longer than for most 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7737CC47-FB47-4DAF-87C2-18950BAD40FA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus Poey 1860:307" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rivulus</taxonomicName>
while the dorsal and ventral rays are extended to an even greater degree in mature males. Thus, it is the first record of a 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7737CC47-FB47-4DAF-87C2-18950BAD40FA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus Poey 1860:307" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rivulus</taxonomicName>
species with an exaggerated lyre tail. The dorsal and anal fin rays are also uniquely elongated. The longest anal fin rays of mature males are at least 150% of the body depth at anal fin origin, whereas in all other known species of the genus they are less than 100% of the body depth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="4">Coloration</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageNumber="5" pageNumber="4">Live colors. Male: The sides are blue reflective and show five or six continuous lines. The three upper lines are red. The lower lip is black and a wide stripe runs via the eyes to the gill covers where it splits into two lines and ends at anal fin height. These two lower lines are more dark red to black on the sides before they merge to one red band posterior to the anal fin and continue through the mid-lower portion of the caudal fin. The lyre shaped caudal fin has the following color pattern. There is a yellow stripe along the dorsal margin which continues to the end of the dorsal extension, followed interiorly by a blue stripe and then a red one. The ventral margin of the caudal is also yellow which continues to the end of the ventral extension, followed interiorly by a blue stripe and then a red one. The middle part of the caudal is greenish. The elongated dorsal fin is reflective blue with a many red spots. The elongated anal fin is yellow distally and blue basally with a few red spots. The ventral fins are yellow with some red spots. The pectoral fins are clear. The dorsum is brown and the belly is dirty white.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="7">
Female: dorsum and sides are light brown with irregular dark spots that form a pattern of diagonal bands. There is a black band on the lower lip, which runs, as in the males, via the eye to the lower part of the base of the caudal fin. Above this band there are two lines of indistinct red spots. The caudal fin is clear and shows irregular black markings that form three vertical-lines. On each fin ray between the vertical-lines is a light yellow spot. Females also have an ocellus on the dorsal part of the caudal peduncle. This ocellus is often present in females of many species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7737CC47-FB47-4DAF-87C2-18950BAD40FA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus Poey 1860:307" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rivulus</taxonomicName>
and hence is often called a “ 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7737CC47-FB47-4DAF-87C2-18950BAD40FA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus Poey 1860:307" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rivulus</taxonomicName>
spot”. The proximal 1/3 of the anal fin is light blue with two rows of dark spots. The distal 2/3 is dark red. The dorsal fin is clear with irregular red spots. The ventral and pectoral fins are clear.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="7">Color in alcohol. Males: Sides are light brown, on the lower part there are two or three rows of dark red spots, no longitudinal band is visible. All fins are clear without spots. Females are light brown with darker brown spots with no visible longitudinal stripe. All fins are clear, except the caudal fin, which has the same pattern as in life.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="7">
The 
<typeStatus>holotype</typeStatus>
and allotype have a D type pattern of frontal scalation (sensu Hoedeman 1958). The other specimens were not examined for this character as it is no longer used in diagnostic keys.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="7">Etymology</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mahdiaensis">Rivulus mahdiaensis</taxonomicName>
is named after the village Mahdia near where it was discovered.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="7">Distribution and habitat</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="7">
The type locality of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mahdiaensis">Rivulus mahdiaensis</taxonomicName>
is a small black water creek, called Blackwater Creek, near the village of Mahdia. This creek is a tributary of the Potaro River, 4 miles above Kangaruma landing, on the right bank of the Potaro River, Mazaruni-Potaro District, Guyana. The location is about 250 meters above sea level.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mahdiaensis">Rivulus mahdiaensis</taxonomicName>
was collected in the shallow parts of this black water forest-creek between the roots of plants growing at the bank of the creek (Fig. 2). We also caught them in little pools along the banks of the creek. They prefer the dark parts of the biotope. 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:9E74E99A-0F37-473B-A742-8C1E1423A54A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus waimacui Eigenmann 1909:50" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="waimacui">Rivulus waimacui</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Apistogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ortmanni">Apistogramma ortmanni</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:9567EE5D-D74B-4687-9D84-379884C2C167" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Nannacara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Nannacara bimaculata Eigenmann 1912:488" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bimaculata">Nannacara bimaculata</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:54834AA8-32DE-4CE5-9D16-3633B3A3FB11" class="Actinopterygii" family="Crenuchidae" genus="Poecilocharax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Poecilocharax bovalii Eigenmann 1909:34" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bovalli">Poecilocharax bovalli</taxonomicName>
were caught in the same creek. The temperature of the water was 25° C. at 14.00 hours. The pH was 4.5 and the Total Dissolved Solids was &lt;1DH.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph lastPageNumber="8" pageNumber="7">
A second location of this new species was found in 1997 along the road between Bartica and Garraway Stream by the author and his wife Y. Suijker-Jansen, F. Vermeulen and M. Vermeulen. This location is another blackwater creek, north of the Potaro River, which crosses the road from Bartica to Mahdia at 77 miles from Bartica (Fig. 3). No specimens were preserved from this second location. This species may have a very limited distribution or be uncommon where it is found as no other collections of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mahdiaensis">R. mahdiaensis</taxonomicName>
were made at the eight different sites around Mahdia and along the road from Bartica to Mahdia visited during collecting trips of 1991, 1995, and 1997.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageNumber="8">Aquarium behavior</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mahdiaensis">Rivulus mahdiaensis</taxonomicName>
is a peaceful species, which can be kept in a group of several pairs. Sometimes there is some aggression or competition between the males but they do not appear to damage each other. They do not like bright light. The pH of the water must be around 6 and temperature around 23° C. Under aquarium conditions they lay their eggs (~2 mm in diameter) in plants with fine leafs, like 
<taxonomicName class="Gymnolaemata" family="Vesiculariidae" genus="Vesicularia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ctenostomatida" pageNumber="8" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="dubyana">Vesicularia dubyana</taxonomicName>
(Java moss). They will also spawn in artificial spawning mops made of yarn depositing eggs in the top and at the bottom. The eggs develop in 18 to 21 days. The newly hatched fry are immediately able to take 
<taxonomicName class="Branchiopoda" family="Artemiidae" genus="Artemia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anostraca" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Artemia</taxonomicName>
nauplii. Young fish have the plainer pattern of females until ten to twelve weeks of age when the color pattern of males begins to appear.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="8">Discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="8">
One of the hallmarks of the genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7737CC47-FB47-4DAF-87C2-18950BAD40FA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus Poey 1860:307" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rivulus</taxonomicName>
is morphometric homogeneity (Huber, 1992). However, 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mahdiaensis">R. mahdiaensis</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguished from related small species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7737CC47-FB47-4DAF-87C2-18950BAD40FA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus Poey 1860:307" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rivulus</taxonomicName>
by the following criteria. It differs from 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:28242994-BF55-43B9-AA5B-89413344A340" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus breviceps Eigenmann 1909:49" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="breviceps">Rivulus breviceps</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:5667AFB0-869D-44D2-9686-7CBA1A0114EE" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus lyricauda Thomerson, Berkenkamp &amp; Taphorn 1991:290" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lyricauda">Rivulus lyricauda</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:C85063FD-B6D1-4505-A11A-2808251D256A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus agilae Hoedeman 1954:203" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="agilae">Rivulus agilae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="torenticola">
Rivulus torenticola Vermeulen &amp; 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Isbrücker">Isbruecker</normalizedToken>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:6682190D-4BFC-4AB6-B2A1-3A19A95CD22D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus gransabanae Lasso, Taphorn &amp; Thomerson 1992:298" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gransabanae">Rivulus gransabanae Lasso, Taphorn &amp; Thomerson</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:37E63DF1-2EF0-4BA6-BF0B-B292F82522C9" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus frenatus Eigenmann 1912:453, 455" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="frenatus">Rivulus frenatus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:80210F02-FBC9-4A97-A95B-296874194674" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus xiphidius Huber 1979:66" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="xiphidius">Rivulus xiphidius</taxonomicName>
by its lower number of dorsal and anal fin rays as well as a more anterior insertion of the dorsal fin relative to the anal fin (D/A metric of Huber, 1992). The low number of lateral line scales (30) in 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mahdiaensis">R. mahdiaensis</taxonomicName>
is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:5667AFB0-869D-44D2-9686-7CBA1A0114EE" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus lyricauda Thomerson, Berkenkamp &amp; Taphorn 1991:290" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lyricauda">R. lyricauda</taxonomicName>
(30.6) and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:80210F02-FBC9-4A97-A95B-296874194674" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus xiphidius Huber 1979:66" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="xiphidius">R. xiphidius</taxonomicName>
while this number averages greater than 31 for the other species listed above (Huber 1992) (Table 2). Females of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mahdiaensis">R. mahdiaensis</taxonomicName>
have a caudal ocellus as do 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:C85063FD-B6D1-4505-A11A-2808251D256A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus agilae Hoedeman 1954:203" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="agilae">R. agilae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:FBA3D378-1C49-443A-A0E2-E8F9EE0E5BE4" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus geayi Vaillant 1899:156 [3]" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="geayi">R. geayi</taxonomicName>
. However, it is lacking in females of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:5667AFB0-869D-44D2-9686-7CBA1A0114EE" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus lyricauda Thomerson, Berkenkamp &amp; Taphorn 1991:290" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lyricauda">R. lyricauda</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:37E63DF1-2EF0-4BA6-BF0B-B292F82522C9" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus frenatus Eigenmann 1912:453, 455" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="frenatus">R. frenatus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:80210F02-FBC9-4A97-A95B-296874194674" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus xiphidius Huber 1979:66" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="xiphidius">R. xiphidius</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:6682190D-4BFC-4AB6-B2A1-3A19A95CD22D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus gransabanae Lasso, Taphorn &amp; Thomerson 1992:298" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gransabanae">R. gransabanae</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="torenticola">R. torenticola</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mahdiaensis">R. mahdiaensis</taxonomicName>
also differs from all of these species by body shape, shape of anal and dorsal fin and shape and color pattern of the caudal fin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mahdiaensis">R. mahdiaensis</taxonomicName>
represents a unique and distinct phenotype within the genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7737CC47-FB47-4DAF-87C2-18950BAD40FA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus Poey 1860:307" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rivulus</taxonomicName>
. The color pattern, especially that of the female, suggested a relationship with 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:37E63DF1-2EF0-4BA6-BF0B-B292F82522C9" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus frenatus Eigenmann 1912:453, 455" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="frenatus">R. frenatus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:80210F02-FBC9-4A97-A95B-296874194674" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus xiphidius Huber 1979:66" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="xiphidius">R. xiphidius</taxonomicName>
, as females of these species also are characterized by a broad, dark longitudinal stripe on the sides. The broad dark longitudinal stripe also appears in 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:5667AFB0-869D-44D2-9686-7CBA1A0114EE" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus lyricauda Thomerson, Berkenkamp &amp; Taphorn 1991:290" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lyricauda">R. lyricauda</taxonomicName>
when it is stressed (Thomerson et al. 1991). Although 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:5667AFB0-869D-44D2-9686-7CBA1A0114EE" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus lyricauda Thomerson, Berkenkamp &amp; Taphorn 1991:290" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lyricauda">R. lyricauda</taxonomicName>
has modest extensions to the dorsal and ventral rays of the caudal, these extensions are not as long as those of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mahdiaensis">R. mahdiaensis</taxonomicName>
nor are the rays of all unpaired fins as elongated. All four of these species are also characterized by having very dark to black lips.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="9">
The molecular phylogeny of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mahdiaensis">R. mahdiaensis</taxonomicName>
and some of its related species reveals considerable congruence with the morphological features discussed above (Fig. 4). The closest relative among the species sampled is 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:5667AFB0-869D-44D2-9686-7CBA1A0114EE" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus lyricauda Thomerson, Berkenkamp &amp; Taphorn 1991:290" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lyricauda">R. lyricauda</taxonomicName>
, the only other species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7737CC47-FB47-4DAF-87C2-18950BAD40FA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus Poey 1860:307" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rivulus</taxonomicName>
with a clear tendency to form a lyre shaped caudal fin. These two sister taxa are members of a monophyletic group that also includes 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:37E63DF1-2EF0-4BA6-BF0B-B292F82522C9" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus frenatus Eigenmann 1912:453, 455" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="frenatus">R. frenatus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:80210F02-FBC9-4A97-A95B-296874194674" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus xiphidius Huber 1979:66" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="xiphidius">R xiphidius</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:C85063FD-B6D1-4505-A11A-2808251D256A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus agilae Hoedeman 1954:203" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="agilae">R. agilae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:FBA3D378-1C49-443A-A0E2-E8F9EE0E5BE4" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus geayi Vaillant 1899:156 [3]" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="geayi">R. geayi</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:BA19ADC4-748C-4C20-A89D-FE97834A03ED" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus strigatus Regan 1912:502" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="strigatus">R. strigatus</taxonomicName>
. [We are aware that 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:BA19ADC4-748C-4C20-A89D-FE97834A03ED" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus strigatus Regan 1912:502" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="strigatus">R. strigatus Regan</taxonomicName>
has been synonymized with 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:FBA3D378-1C49-443A-A0E2-E8F9EE0E5BE4" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus geayi Vaillant 1899:156 [3]" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="geayi">R. geayi</taxonomicName>
(Huber 1992), however the two geographically distinct populations used for the DNA sequencing (Guyana and Belem, Brazil) displayed significant sequence differences and we retained the name 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:BA19ADC4-748C-4C20-A89D-FE97834A03ED" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus strigatus Regan 1912:502" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="strigatus">strigatus</taxonomicName>
in Fig. 4]
</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageNumber="12" pageNumber="11">
The ten taxa represented in Figure 4 and rooted in that figure with 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:C47820AF-90FE-42EB-8652-8318502EF70D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus cylindraceus Poey 1860:308, 383" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cylindraceus">R. cylindraceus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:535A2721-6F55-45AB-958D-D01DBFECFCFB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus roloffi Roloff 1938:597" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="roloffi">R. roloffi</taxonomicName>
when placed in the larger context of the family Rivulidae, represents a monophyletic clade that diverged from other members of the family early in its history (Murphy et al., 1999: Hrbek and Larsen, 1999). 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:28242994-BF55-43B9-AA5B-89413344A340" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus breviceps Eigenmann 1909:49" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="breviceps">Rivulus breviceps</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:6682190D-4BFC-4AB6-B2A1-3A19A95CD22D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus gransabanae Lasso, Taphorn &amp; Thomerson 1992:298" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gransabanae">R. gransabanae</taxonomicName>
are also members of this group based upon independent sequence data (Hrbek et al., 2004), but were not available for inclusion in this analysis. 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="torenticola">Rivulus torenticola</taxonomicName>
may also be a member of this group.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="12">
The reduced chromosome number seen for 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mahdiaensis">R. mahdiaensis</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 5a) is an unusual karyotype in that 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7737CC47-FB47-4DAF-87C2-18950BAD40FA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus Poey 1860:307" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rivulus</taxonomicName>
karyotypes rarely show reduction in chromosome number below 2n=44 (Scheel 1972, Collier, unpublished data). However, within the group of ten taxa shown in Figure 4, most members have reduced chromosome numbers. This reduction is minimal for three species in this clade which have most recently diverged from each other [
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:C85063FD-B6D1-4505-A11A-2808251D256A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus agilae Hoedeman 1954:203" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="agilae">R. agilae</taxonomicName>
is 2n=44 (Zoch et al. 1989), 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:FBA3D378-1C49-443A-A0E2-E8F9EE0E5BE4" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus geayi Vaillant 1899:156 [3]" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="geayi">R. geayi</taxonomicName>
is 2n=42 (Fig. 5f), 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:BA19ADC4-748C-4C20-A89D-FE97834A03ED" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus strigatus Regan 1912:502" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="strigatus">R. strigatus</taxonomicName>
from Belem is 2n=42 (Fig. 5e)], whereas it is more pronounced for 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mahdiaensis">R. mahdiaensis</taxonomicName>
and the three other related species [
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mahdiaensis">R. mahdiaensis</taxonomicName>
is 2n=38 (Fig. 5a), 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:5667AFB0-869D-44D2-9686-7CBA1A0114EE" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus lyricauda Thomerson, Berkenkamp &amp; Taphorn 1991:290" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lyricauda">R. lyricauda</taxonomicName>
is 2n=40 (Fig. 5b), 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:37E63DF1-2EF0-4BA6-BF0B-B292F82522C9" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus frenatus Eigenmann 1912:453, 455" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="frenatus">R. frenatus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:80210F02-FBC9-4A97-A95B-296874194674" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus xiphidius Huber 1979:66" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="xiphidius">R. xiphidius</taxonomicName>
are both 2n=30 (Fig. 5c &amp; d),]. Within this latter group 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mahdiaensis">R. mahdiaensis</taxonomicName>
